            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">The items in this collection are chiefly by William West Long and Morgan Calhoun and are accompanied by notes of Speck with numbers and descriptions made by John Witthoft. There are diaries of William West Long, Gadugi (a Cherokee mutual aid group) accounts, Big Cove birth and death records, and material collected by James Mooney in 1887. There is also material on medicine, including formulae, curing charms, and texts. Cherokee-English vocabularies and personal accounts by Speck are included.</abstract>
